By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) – The Managing Director of Medview Airline, Mr. Muneer Bankole has reportedly been taken into custody by the Economic and Financial Crimes Commission, (EFCC). He was reportedly detained this afternoon at the headquarters of the EFCC in Jabi, Abuja. A source familiar with case disclosed that Bankole who arrived the EFCC complex at 11am on Monday, January 31, 2022, was invited by the anti-graft agency over a case of alleged diversion of 50 percent of funds paid to him by the National Hajj Commission, and additional $900,000 USD, for the airlift of pilgrims in 2019. He allegedly received the funds as mobilization but did not execute the contract. When contacted, EFCC Spokesman, Wilson Uwujaren, confirmed the arrest. By Adekunle Williams & Solomon Asowata Lagos  -  Medview Airline, one of Nigeria’s fastest growing flag carriers, will be listed by introduction on the Nigerian Stock Exchange (NSE) on Jan. 31, a senior official said on Sunday in Lagos. Medview’s Executive Director, Business Development, Mr Isiaq Na-Allah,said the listing would… In "Business" By Adekunle Williams   Lagos   -    A Nigerian carrier, Medview Airline, has taken delivery of its newly acquired B777-200ER, to boost its fleet. The News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) reports that the aircraft, with registration number – 5N-BVY – touched down at about 8.00 a.m. on Thursday at the Murtala… In "News" By Salisu Sani-Idris Abuja  -   The National Hajj Commission of Nigeria (NAHCON) has directed State Pilgrims Welfare Boards, Agencies and Commissions to extend deadline for the payment of the 2017 Hajj fare by one week. The Executive Chairman of NAHCON, Alhaji Abdullahi Mohammad gave the directive at the contract signing… In "News"